            <div class="molecule"></div>
            <div class="molecule"></div>
            <div class="molecule"></div>
            <div class="molecule"></div>
            <span style="z-index: 10; font-size: 40px;">üß´</span>
          </div>
          <div style="font-size: var(--text-2xl); color: var(--text-muted);">‚Üí</div>
          <div style="text-align: center; color: var(--text-secondary);">
            <div style="font-size: var(--text-4xl); margin-bottom: var(--space-2);">‚òï</div>
            <div style="font-size: var(--text-sm);">No stirring required</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card-content" style="padding: var(--space-6);">
          <h2 style="font-size: var(--text-2xl); margin-bottom: var(--space-4); color: var(--text-primary);">
            The Invisible Current
          </h2>

          <p class="text-secondary" style="line-height: var(--leading-relaxed); font-size: var(--text-lg); margin-bottom: var(--space-4);">
            You drop sugar into your tea. You don't stir, yet five minutes later, every sip is sweet. No energy expended, no proteins involved‚Äîjust physics.
          </p>

          <p class="text-secondary" style="line-height: var(--leading-relaxed); margin-bottom: var(--space-4);">
            Your cells perform this same trick <strong>2 trillion times per second</strong>, moving oxygen and nutrients without spending a single ATP molecule. But there's a catch: they can't control where it goes.
          </p>

          <div style="background: var(--bg-elevated); padding: var(--space-4); border-radius: var(--radius-md); border-left: 4px solid var(--secondary-dark);">
            <p style="font-weight: var(--weight-semibold); color: var(--text-primary);">
              <i data-lucide="help-circle" style="width: 20px; height: 20px; display: inline-block; vertical-align: middle; margin-right: var(--space-2);"></i>
              Inquiry Question: How do cells move substances without energy?
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- 2. CORE UNIT 1: Simple Diffusion -->
      <section class="section" data-section="unit1">
        <h2 class="section-title">Unit 1: Simple Diffusion ‚Äì Down the Gradient</h2>

        <!-- Visual-First -->
        <div class="diagram-zone">
          <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: var(--space-6); width: 100%; max-width: 500px;">
            <div style="flex: 1; text-align: center; padding: var(--space-4); background: rgba(255,201,150,0.3); border-radius: var(--radius-md);">
              <div style="font-size: var(--text-3xl); margin-bottom: var(--space-2);">‚óè‚óè‚óè‚óè‚óè</div>
              <div style="font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--text-muted);">High Concentration</div>
              <div style="font-size: var(--text-xs); color: var(--text-muted);">(Many molecules)</div>
            </div>
            <div style="font-size: var(--text-2xl); color: var(--secondary-dark);">‚Üí</div>
            <div style="flex: 1; text-align: center; padding: var(--space-4); background: rgba(147,228,249,0.3); border-radius: var(--radius-md);">
              <div style="font-size: var(--text-3xl); margin-bottom: var(--space-2);">‚óè</div>
              <div style="font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--text-muted);">Low Concentration</div>
              <div style="font-size: var(--text-xs); color: var(--text-muted);">(Few molecules)</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p style="margin-top: var(--space-4); color: var(--text-muted); font-size: var(--text-sm);">
            Net movement from high to low concentration
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Verbal-Visual Integration -->
        <div class="content-card">
          <div class="content-card__header">
            <div class="content-card__icon" style="background: #f0fdf4; color: #16a34a;">üéØ</div>
            <h3 class="content-card__title">The Concentration Gradient</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="content-card__body">
            <p class="text-secondary" style="line-height: var(--leading-relaxed); margin-bottom: var(--space-4);">
              This diagram shows <strong>simple diffusion</strong>: the net movement of particles from an area of <span style="color: #ea580c; font-weight: 600;">high concentration</span> to <span style="color: #0891b2; font-weight: 600;">low concentration</span>.
            </p>
            <p class="text-secondary" style="line-height: var(--leading-relaxed); margin-bottom: var(--space-4);">
              <strong>Key Principle:</strong> This is <em>passive</em>‚Äîit requires no metabolic energy (ATP). The cell doesn't "do" anything; the laws of thermodynamics drive the movement.
            </p>
            <div style="background: var(--bg-elevated); padding: var(--space-4); border-radius: var(--radius-md);">
              <p style="font-weight: var(--weight-semibold); color: var(--text-primary); margin-bottom: var(--space-2);">
                Biological Example:
              </p>
              <p class="text-secondary" style="font-size: var(--text-sm);">
                Oxygen diffuses from lungs (high O‚ÇÇ) into blood (lower O‚ÇÇ). Carbon dioxide diffuses out. Both follow their concentration gradients.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Checkpoint -->
