        <p style="margin: 0;">
          <strong>Lesson 4 Connection:</strong> Remember the phospholipid bilayer? It blocks hydrophilic substances. So how do glucose or amino acids enter? They can't simply diffuse through the oily center‚Äîthey need help. This is where <strong>facilitated diffusion</strong> bridges the gap between simple diffusion and the membrane structure.
        </p>
